Always-Less-Effort method

Always Less Effort (ALE) defines a workload scheduling method that enforces a monotonically decreasing daily effort profile over a fixed deadline.
The workload distribution is parameterized by a user-defined initial-to-final ratio and derived via a closed-form analytical solution.

Algorithms, use cases, output examples, and mathematical formulations are provided herein.

